     A triangle is specified by supplying a list of six numbers:

      (x, y, ğ˜…, ğ˜†, ğ•©, ğ•ª)

     where (x, y), (ğ˜…, ğ˜†) and (ğ•©, ğ•ª) are the coordinates of the vertices of the
     triangle.

